821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":23,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":34,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":36,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When John Harsnett was born in 1535, in Hertfordshire, England, his father, John Harsnett, was 20 and his mother, Cyshye Beck, was 36. He married Jeanelle Murphy in 1559, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died from 1565 to 1572, in his hometown."},"et":{"1535–from 1565 to 1572":"1535–1565 kuni 1572","1535–1572":"1535–1572","1535–Male":"1535–Surnud","1539–1602":"1539–1602","1540–Female":"1540–Surnud","1570–1620":"1570–1620","1541–1573":"1541–1573","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1500–1565":"1500–1565","December 1541":"detsember 1541","1572":"157